# collecting review scores and dates for all reviews with review text 

dates = []
overall = []

for review in originalreviews:
    score = review['overall']
    for field in review:
        if 'reviewText' in field:
            date = review['reviewTime']            
            dates.append(date)
            overall.append(score)

months = []
days = []
years = []
reviewdates = []

for date in dates:
    month, day, year = date.split(' ')
    day = day.replace(',','')
    months.append(month)
    days.append(day)    
    years.append(year)
    reviewdates.append([int(month),int(day),int(year)])
    
dates_df = pd.DataFrame(reviewdates, columns=['month','day','year'])
yeardist_df = pd.DataFrame(dates_df.year.value_counts()).rename(columns = {'year':'no. of reviews'}).sort_index()
overall_df = pd.DataFrame(overall, columns=['score'])
overalldist_df = pd.DataFrame(overall_df.score.value_counts()).rename(columns = {'score':'no. of reviews'}).sort_index()

#Reviewer Frequent or not frequent
def define_frequency (row):
    if row['reviewer_frequency'] > 25 :
        return 'Frequent'
    elif row['reviewer_frequency'] < 25 :
        return 'Not Frequent'
    elif row['reviewer_frequency'] == 25 :
        return 'Neutral'
    return 'Not Frequent'


overall_df['IsFrequentReviewer'] = overall_df.apply(lambda row: define_frequency (row), axis=1)

# part of speech based on penn treebank
# https://www.sketchengine.eu/tagsets/penn-treebank-tagset/
verbs = ['VB','VBD','VBG','VBN', 'VBP', 'VBZ', 'VH', 'VHD', 'VHG',
        'VHN', 'VHP', 'VHZ', 'VV', 'VVD', 'VVG','VVN', 'VVP', 'VVZ']
nouns = ['NN', 'NNS', 'NP', 'NPS']
adverbs = ['RB', 'RBR', 'RBS']
adjectives = ['JJ', 'JJR', 'JJS'] 

# creating a pos_tag mapping function to nltk lemmatizer

def posmap(partofspeech):
    if partofspeech in verbs:
        partofspeech = 'v'
    elif partofspeech in nouns:
        partofspeech = 'n'
    elif partofspeech in adverbs:
        partofspeech = 'r'
    elif partofspeech in adjectives:
        partofspeech = 'a'
    else:
        partofspeech = None
    return partofspeech;
In [122]:
# special words
def special(specialword):
    if specialword == 'zero':
        specialword = '0'
    elif specialword == 'one':
        specialword = '1'
    elif specialword == 'two':
        specialword = '2'
    elif specialword == 'three':
        specialword = '3'
    elif specialword == 'four':
        specialword = '4'
    elif specialword == 'five':
        specialword = '5'
    elif specialword == 'six':
        specialword = '6'
    elif specialword == 'seven':
        specialword = '7'
    elif specialword == 'eight':
        specialword = '8'
    elif specialword == 'nine':
        specialword = '9'
    elif specialword == 'ten':
        specialword = '10'
    else: specialword = specialword
    return specialword;

# correcting two-word variations to one, punctuation and special character drop 

def chardrop(review):
    temp_list = [n for n in punctuation]
    review = review.lower().replace(' o.k. ',' okay ')
    review = review.lower().replace(' ok ', ' okay ')
    for n in temp_list:
        review = review.replace(n,' ')
    return(review);

In [126]:
wordlist = []
cleanreviews = []
cleanwords = []
words = str()
start_time = time.time()

for review in balancedreviews:
    for word in nltk.word_tokenize(chardrop(review[0])):
        word = special(word)
        wordlist.append(word)
    for pair in pos_tag(wordlist):
        posword = pair[0]
        pos = posmap(pair[1])
        if posmap(pair[1]) == None:
            word = WordNetLemmatizer().lemmatize(posword)
        else:
            word = WordNetLemmatizer().lemmatize(posword,pos)
        if word in negation:
            word = 'not'
        if word not in text_stopwords:
            cleanwords.append(word)
            cleanstring = ' '.join([str(word) for word in cleanwords])
            cleanstring = cleanstring.translate(words.maketrans("","",string.punctuation))                       
    cleanreviews.append((cleanstring,review[1]))
    wordlist = []
    cleanwords = []
    cleanstring = str()
    
print("--- %s seconds ---" % (time.time() - start_time))

#K-means clustering
#TF-IDF vectorizer
vec = TfidfVectorizer(stop_words="english")
vec.fit(cleaned_dframe['Review'])
features = vec.transform(cleaned_dframe['Review'])
#returns a list of words
words = vec.get_feature_names()


kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters = 7, n_init = 17, n_jobs = 1, tol = 0.01, max_iter = 200)
#fit the data 
kmeans.fit(features)
#transforms the numbers back into words
common_words = kmeans.cluster_centers_.argsort()[:,-1:-11:-1]
for num, centroid in enumerate(common_words):
    print(str(num) + ' : ' + ', '.join(words[word] for word in centroid))
